(54, 'El-SUV-electrico-mas-vendido-en-Espana-y-mucho-mejor-que-el-Dacia-Spring', 'El SUV eléctrico más vendido en España y mucho mejor que el Dacia Spring', 'Seguimos repasando los coches más vendidos en enero de 2022 y ahora es el turno de los coches 100% eléctricos. Un sector que va claramente al alza y en el que hay un claro favorito por encima del resto. Un coche mucho mejor que el Dacia Spring, el eléctrico más barato por excelencia, que sin […]', 'Seguimos repasando los coches más vendidos en enero de 2022 y ahora es el turno de los coches 100% eléctricos. Un sector que va claramente al alza y en el que hay un claro favorito por encima del resto. Un coche mucho mejor que el Dacia Spring, el eléctrico más barato por excelencia, que sin embargo no aparece en el top 5 de los más vendidos. Enero cerró con un total de 2.188 matriculaciones de coches eléctricos. Esto se traduce en un soberbio crecimiento del 254,05%. En este aumento tiene que ver el crecimiento de opciones en este sector, así como a vigencia de las ayudas del Plan MOVES III. Dacia Spring Las ventas de coches eléctricos suben en España Por otro lado, la cuota de coches eléctricos en España se sitúa ahora en el 4,22%. Mientras que las matriculaciones de turismos alcanzaron las 1.777 operaciones, que significan un 258,99% más respecto a 2021. Entrando en detalles, el modelo eléctrico más vendido en enero de 2022 fue el Kia e-Niro. El todocamino surcoreano alcanzó las 223 matriculaciones. Una cifra con la que se destaca sobre el resto, pues el segundo clasificado se quedó en casi la mitad de las ventas del e-Niro. Se trata del MINI Cooper SE, que matriculó 122 unidades. El tercer puesto fue para el Hyundai IONIQ 5. Kia e-Niro Ni rastro del Dacia Spring en el top 5 Kia vuelve a aparecer en el cuarto puesto con el EV6, mientras que Hyundai repite en la quinta posición con el Kona eléctrico. Posición Modelo Uds. vendidas enero 2022 1 KIA e-Niro 223 2 MINI Cooper SE 122 3 Hyundai IONIQ 5 102 4 KIA EV6 92 5 Hyundai Kona Eléctrico 89 Una lista en la que sorprende que no aparezca el Dacia Spring, el coche eléctrico más barato que se puede comprar en la actualidad. Está claro que quien compra un coche eléctrico prima la calidad, las posibilidades y las prestaciones por encima de si es más o menos barato. El Spring solo alcanza 44 CV de potencia. Y tampoco aparece el Tesla Model 3, uno de los modelos eléctricos más vendidos de 2021.', NULL, NULL, 'https://motor.eldesmarque.com/noticias/1360989-el-suv-electrico-mas-vendido-en-espana-y-mucho-mejor-que-el-dacia-spring', '2022-02-12 06:29:32', 'mexico', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 1, 'Noticias;Dacia;Kia e-Niro;Spring', NULL, 0),
(55, 'The-Masked-Singer-UK:-Who-is-Robobunny-All-the-clues-and-theories', 'The Masked Singer UK: Who is Robobunny? All the clues and theories', 'Who could it be?', 'Robobunny’s costume is a feast for the eyes (Picture: Vincent Dolman/Bandicoot TV/ITV/PA) The Masked Singer UK has had the nation putting their guesses hats on, particularly when it comes to star performer Robobunny in season 3 of the hit ITV show. The bizarre character has won viewers over with their performances, including their heart-melting cover of Saving All My Love For You by Whitney Houston. Judges Rita Ora, Mo Gilligan, Jonathan Ross, and Davina McCall have been left wracking their brains by the performances as they tried to guess which celebrity could be under the costume. Robobunny has now made it to the final alongside Panda and Mushroom, meaning that their identity will soon be revealed. So what are all of the clues and theories so far pointing towards the star who’s taken on the Robobunny persona? Let’s break them down. All the clues and theories for Robobunny so far Clues from episode 1 They initially had a cockney-sounding accent, which the judges thought might be fake.They’re a ‘real softie who’s part of a machine’.Peroxide polish was sprayed on the character. Perhaps a hint of their hair colour in real life?They have ‘hard exteriors’.They’re ‘here to control or delete what you know about me’.Their final clue during episode one was: ‘I might be made of metal, but that doesn’t stop me making a splash. Clues from episode 3 In their second VT, Robobunny entered a warehouse where a police badge, cowboy boots, a Native American headdress and a builder’s hat could be seen. While the judges initially thought they might be an actor, Mo then pointed out that each of the objects related to musical group the Village People.Robobunny said: ‘Nothing makes me happier than standing at my deck with nothing around me but a little bit of country,’ prompting the judges to think they could be from another country.They also revealed they love a bit of a dance, referencing line dancing. For their two lies and a truth, Robobunny said… These metal shoes are made for more than moonwalking.I’m not one for revenge, but I’ll always get payback.It was a knockout performance that launched my career. Clues from episode 5 The VT opened with Robobunny doing some gardening, hinting at it being a pastime of theirs.They said: ‘Rabbits come from big families, this bunny is no exception’ – so what big families in showbiz can you think of?Their dad – ‘Papa Bunny’ – is said to have ‘inspired their talent’, so it looks like their father could also be well-known.A pair of boxing gloves were seen embellished with the initials ‘MA’ – which some think could stand for boxing legend ‘Muhammad Ali’.They also referenced the ‘gospel truth’, so they could have a background in gospel music.Robobunny also said that people often remark: ‘Isn’t she good’ – so are they a female celebrity after all? Clues from episode 6 Cup of Joe – maybe a famous Joe or someone who has starred in Joseph References to ‘diva’Needs time to rest or will shut down completely Is someone who has reinvented themselves References to Grease – someone who has appeared in the musical, maybe? Clues from episode 7 Year 3000 – reference to Busted?Being able to put things in his own words is importantSoars to Great Heights Lots of references to rocketsImmortalised in Hall of FameHas circumnavigated the world 10 times Who do you think Robobunny could be? (Picture: ITV) So who have the judges picked as possible singers behind the mask for Robobunny? Which celebrities have been guessed so far? Mark Feehily Many people think it’s Mark Feehily behind the mask (Picture: Christie Goodwin/Getty Images) Many viewers are convinced that Robobunny is Westlife singer Mark Feehily. Several said that they recognised his voice instantly, while others pointed out that the clues mentioning line dancing might have been a connection to his home in Sligo, which had its own ranch. Vinnie Jones We wouldn’t be surprised if Vinnie was revealed behind the mask (Picture: Rodin Eckenroth/Getty Images) Someone with a hard exterior who’s really soft on the inside – of course Vinnie Jones comes to mind. People may be surprised to know that he also has a musical past, releasing his single Wooly Bully in 1993 and his album Respect in 2002. Drake Could Drake really have decided to come on Masked Singer UK? (Picture: Christopher Polk/Getty Images for Coachella) Mention of Robobunny having ‘control’ made the judges connect the dots to Drake’s song Controlla, from his fourth studio album Views. Paddy McGuinness Will the judges decide no likey, no lighty? (Picture: Matthew McNulty/Getty Images) All of the mechanics making up Robobunny’s costume could be a hint at another show featuring machinery… aka Top Gear, of which Paddy McGuinness is a presenter. Elon Musk To be honest, Robobunny seems like a likely alter ego for Elon Musk (Picture: Pascal Le Segretain/Getty Images) When you look at Robobunny, and imagine a famous individual who’s heavily involved with robots, of course your thoughts are going to drift to Elon Musk, the CEO of Tesla. Jeremy Clarkson Has Jeremy swapped his farm for the stage (Picture: David M. Benett/Getty Images) Another man involved in a car series, former Top Gear host Jeremy Clarkson, who since moved on to present The Grand Tour after his departure from the aforementioned programme. Billy Ray Cyrus Billy Ray Cyrus is a Grammy Award-winning artist (Picture by Frazer Harrison/Getty Images) During Robobunny’s second appearance, their VT made several references to country music and dancing. So of course, Billy Ray Cyrus, the Achy Breaky Heart singer, received a mention. Danny O’Donoghue The Script were first formed in 2007 (Picture: Rob Harrison/Getty Images) Rita’s train of thought led her to Danny O’Donoghue from The Script. Several symbols in Robobunny’s VT hinted at the singer being an actor, with the judge stating that actor’s read scripts, and therefore the singer could be none other than Danny from The Script. Richard Blackwood Richard Blackwood is a friend of Mo’s (Picture: Andrew Benge/Getty Images) Mo took a look at Robobunny’s name, taking the letters RB, which lead him to the assumption that it could be his friend, actor and rapper Richard Blackwood, who he described as an ‘all-round entertainer’. Kevin Bacon Could it be the Footloose star? (Picture: Frederick M. Brown/Getty Images) With all the references to line dancing in Robobunny’s video, it shouldn’t have been surprising that Kevin Bacon, who starred in the 1984 classic film Footloose, would be put forward as a suggestion. Will Smith Could it be the Fresh Prince behind the mask? (Picture: Axelle/Bauer-Griffin/FilmMagic) Not only did Will Smith play Muhammad Ali in a biopic – which could be referenced by the MA boxing gloves in a Robobunny VT – but he also has an established music career. Jason Derulo Jason has the voice and the moves (Picture: Bryan Bedder/Getty Images for GQ) Having performed Dynamite by BTS on The Masked Singer UK, Jonathan put forward the idea that it could be Jason Derulo, considering the singer had a hit with the band. What do you think? The Masked Singer UK concludes tonight at 7pm on ITV. The Masked Singer 2022: All the clues and theories so far Who is Bagpipes? - PAT CASH Who is Chandelier? - HEATHER SMALL Who is Doughnuts? - MICHAEL OWEN Who is Firework? - JAIME WINSTONE Who is Lionfish? - WILL YOUNG Who is Mushroom? Who is Panda? Who is Poodle? - TOM CHAPLIN Who is Robobunny? Who is Rockhopper? - MICHELLE WILLIAMS Who is Snow Leopard? - GLORIA HUNNIFORD Who is Traffic Cone? - ALED JONES Got a story? If you’ve got a celebrity story, video or pictures get in touch with the Metro.co.uk entertainment team by emailing us celebtips@metro.co.uk, calling 020 3615 2145 or by visiting our Submit Stuff page – we’d love to hear from you. MORE : The Masked Singer UK: Jonathan Ross admits judges don’t always recognise unmasked celebs MORE : Joel Dommett ‘lost his mind’ over The Masked Singer finale reveal: ‘It comes out of nowhere’ Follow Metro across our social channels, on Facebook, Twitter and Instagram Share your views in the comments below', 'https://metro.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/PRI_213266168.jpg?quality=90&strip=all', NULL, 'https://metro.co.uk/2022/02/12/the-masked-singer-uk-who-is-robobunny-all-the-clues-and-theories-16094699/', '2022-02-12 06:04:12', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 2, 'TV;ITV;The Masked Singer', NULL, 0),
(56, 'The-troubled-California-factory-at-Tesla\'s-core', 'The troubled California factory at Tesla\'s core', 'Tesla can hardly make enough electric vehicles to meet booming demand, but behind the world\'s most valuable auto brand is its troubled California factory that makes most of those cars.', NULL, 'https://scx1.b-cdn.net/csz/news/tmb/2022/california-has-sued-te.jpg', NULL, 'https://techxplore.com/news/2022-02-california-factory-tesla-core.html', '2022-02-12 04:39:06', 'united states of america', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 3, NULL, NULL, 0),
(57, 'Tesla-manufacturing-in-China-and-selling-in-India-not-digestible:-Gadkari', 'Tesla manufacturing in China and selling in India not digestible: Gadkari', 'New Delhi, February 12 Union Minister for Road Transport and Highways Nitin Gadkari has said that manufacturing Tesla in China and selling in India is not a digestible concept to all of us, as Elon Musk continues to seek tax rebates to sell his electric car in the country. In a media interview, Gadkari said he met the head of the Indian arm of Tesla \"three-four days back\". \"I have tried to convince him. Ultimately it is dependent on him to take the decision (to manufacture in the country),\" Gadkari told News 18. Stressing that Musk has to manufacture here first in order to roll out Tesla cars on the roads, the Minister said: \"Now his (Musk\'s) interest is to manufacture the Tesla car in China and make it sell in India. \"So, if you start here, you are welcome, no problem. But manufacturing in China and selling in India is not a digestible concept to all of us\". When asked about Tesla\'s demand to cut customs duties on electric cars, Gadkari said that the country cannot appease one automobile company. \"India is a huge market. We have all the world\'s automobile giants -- BMW, Volvo, Mercedes-Benz, Toyota, Honda, Hyundai -- present here. If we give one benefit to one company, we have to give that benefit to other companies also. That is the practical problem,\" he elaborated. Musk recently tweeted that he faced challenges from the government for releasing its products in India. \"Tesla isn\'t in India yet due to \"Challenges with the government\", he posted. Tesla has registered its office in Bengaluru as Tesla India Motors and Energy Private Limited and named three directors. The firm is registered with an authorised capital of Rs 15 lakh and paid-up capital of Rs 1 lakh. Earlier this week, the government questioned Tesla\'s business practices of seeking tax breaks to use the Indian market to sell its products, but not wanting to set up manufacturing facilities in the country which can generate thousands of jobs. \"We can\'t grant subsidies or relaxation in taxes to the said company as they don\'t want to set-up their manufacturing and other operation bases here. Why should we favour a company which create jobs in China and mints profit from our markets?\" Minister for Heavy Industries, Krishna Pal Gujjar, told the Lok Sabha in response to a question. \"Our Prime Minister has a vision for all such foreign companies, if you want to sell your product in our country, then manufacture them here only,\" Gujjar added. The minister informed the house that Tesla hasn\'t shown any interest in any of the government\'s schemes for electric vehicles. As per the Ministry of Heavy Industries, the government has formulated a scheme, Faster Adoption and Manufacturing of (Hybrid amp;) Electric Vehicles in India (FAME India) Scheme in 2015 to promote the adoption of electric/hybrid vehicles (EVs) in the country with an aim to reduce dependency on fossil fuels. --IANS', NULL, 'https://englishtribuneimages.blob.core.windows.net/gallary-content/2022/2/2022_2$largeimg_126797464.jpeg', NULL, 'https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/science-technology/tesla-manufacturing-in-china-and-selling-in-india-not-digestible-gadkari-369273', '2022-02-12 04:02:06', 'india', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 3, NULL, NULL, 0),
(58, 'Widziales-jak-kierowcy-Tesli-otwieraja-zamrozone-drzwi-zima-Metoda-na-jaskiniowca-moze-szokowac-WIDEO', 'Widziałeś, jak kierowcy Tesli otwierają zamrożone drzwi zimą? Metoda na jaskiniowca może szokować [WIDEO]', 'W niektórych modelach Tesli nie ma standardowych klamek, które pociągasz, by otworzyć drzwi. Ich właściciele rzekomo korzystają w ten sposób na lepszej aerodynamice, ale zimą mają problem by wsiąść do samochodu. Jak więc sobie radzą? Właściciele Tesli Model 3 i Model Y dzielą się skutecznymi metodami na otwarcie samochodu W dwóch modelach Tesli producent udoskonalił […] The post Widziałeś, jak kierowcy Tesli otwierają zamrożone drzwi zimą? Metoda na jaskiniowca może szokować [WIDEO] appeared first on WRC Motorsport&Beyond.', 'W niektórych modelach Tesli nie ma standardowych klamek, które pociągasz, by otworzyć drzwi. Ich właściciele rzekomo korzystają w ten sposób na lepszej aerodynamice, ale zimą mają problem by wsiąść do samochodu. Jak więc sobie radzą? Właściciele Tesli Model 3 i Model Y dzielą się skutecznymi metodami na otwarcie samochodu W dwóch modelach Tesli producent udoskonalił ważny element nadwozia, jakim są klamki. Zamiast pociągania ich i otwarcia samochodu, kierowcy używają schowanego w drzwiach uchwytu. Wygląda to bardziej elegancko i poprawia aerodynamikę, ale zimą generuje problemy. Co robią kierowcy Tesli Model 3 i Model Y, aby odblokować drzwi, gdy zamarzną? Producent w instrukcji sugeruje użycie siły odpowiadającej tej, z jaką ​​„pukasz do drzwi wejściowych sąsiada”. To ma pozwolić uniknąć wgnieceń w drzwiach Tesli. Co w praktyce stosują kierowcy? Caveman approach to frozen Tesla Model 3 door handle. It’s not a Barbie doll. #tesla #teslamodel3 #model3 #teslawinter pic.twitter.com/5kaY62yVXI — Tesla Canuck (@TeslaCanuck) January 12, 2020 Kiedy nie możesz otworzyć samochodu- dobrze jest odkryć w sobie jaskiniowca Coś, co działa przez wiele lat, nie zawsze wymaga poprawek i ulepszeń, o czym zapomniał amerykański producent. Klamki ukryte w drzwiach samochodu są łatwe w obsłudze pod warunkiem, że nie zamarzną. Bez dźwigni ciężko samochód otworzyć. Kierowcy Tesli Model 3 i Model Y ręcznie otwierają klamki ukryte w drzwiach i na pewno bardzo chcieliby to zmienić. To rozwiązanie w przypadku ujemnych temperatur na zewnętrz sprawia, że dostanie się do wnętrza samochodu, jest niemalże niemożliwe. Kierowcy wówczas sięgają po jedną ze sprawdzonych metod, które zaprezentowali na Twitterze. Mówiąc najprościej, najlepszą metodą jest to by jej po prostu przyłożyć. Brutalna technika dotarcia do wnętrza Tesli, nie przypomina pukania do drzwi sąsiada, a raczej wejście jaskiniowca. Problem solved pic.twitter.com/0fvUKAPBND — Mona M (@Moanaaah) February 6, 2022 Gdybyś miał ocenić kierowców, za kreatywność na pewno spodoba ci się powyższe rozwiązanie. Jest to prawdopodobnie najbardziej widowiskowy sposób wśród rekomendacji właścicieli Tesli bez tradycyjnych klamek. W związku z tym, że potrzeba jest matką wynalazku, na Amazonie można kupić gadżet, który rozwiązuje problem właścicieli Modelu 3 i Modelu Y. Wystarczy zainwestować 45 dolarów, by nie silić się na kreatywność. Tesla opublikowała spektakularne nagranie. Prezentuje kolejny powód, dla którego warto ją kupić [WIDEO]   The post Widziałeś, jak kierowcy Tesli otwierają zamrożone drzwi zimą? Metoda na jaskiniowca może szokować [WIDEO] appeared first on WRC Motorsport&Beyond.', NULL, NULL, 'https://wrc.net.pl/mh-widziales-jak-kierowcy-tesli-otwieraja-zamrozone-drzwi-zima-metoda-na-jaskiniowca-moze-szokowac-wideo', '2022-02-12 03:27:08', 'poland', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 1, 'Moto Newsy;Elon Musk;otwieranie drzwi Tesli zimą;samochód elektryczny;Tesla;tesla model 3;tesla model y', NULL, 0),
(59, 'Soros-buys-stake-in-\'Tesla-killer\'-startup', 'Soros buys stake in ‘Tesla killer’ startup', 'Billionaire George Soros bought $2 billion worth of shares in Amazon-backed electric truck startup Rivian Read Full Article at RT.com', 'The Amazon-backed electric carmaker has yet to produce a consumer vehicle Billionaire investor George Soros bought nearly 20 million shares of electric truck startup Rivian, according to securities filings released on Friday. The shares were worth roughly $2 billion at the time of purchase, making Soros Fund Management one of the firm’s largest investors. Rivian, which is 20% owned by e-commerce giant Amazon, was a hit with investors last fall, when it raised $12 billion in its IPO, becoming the largest market debut of 2021. However, the startup has not yet produced a consumer vehicle. As of December 2021, the carmaker has reportedly delivered just 150 of its electric R1T pickup trucks and only two electric SUVs, the R1S, to customers (mostly employees) with little revenue to report. It is hard to tell when non-employee customers will receive their Rivian cars, but the automaker began notifying non-affiliated reservation holders about when they could expect their vehicles in September last year. In a Rivian Owners forum poll, reservation holders said their R1S delivery dates are between June and September of 2022, while the majority of R1T respondents put down deliveries from March to June. Rivian was due to provide Amazon with more than 100,000 electric trucks last year, but said in December it expected production to fall “a few hundred vehicles short” amid supply chain constraints. READ MORE: \'Tesla killer\' startup shows how to become US’ biggest company earning nothing Apparently due to the failure to deliver on its promises so far, Rivian saw shares drop 43% for the year to date on Friday. The carmaker’s stock price is currently down 67% from the high of $179.46 it reached a week after its IPO debut. For more stories on economy & finance visit RT\'s business section', 'https://cdni.rt.com/files/2022.02/thumbnail/6207679a2030271f1d58d665.jpg', NULL, 'https://www.rt.com/business/549134-rivian-shares-soros-billionaire/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=RSS', '2022-02-12 02:55:22', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 1, NULL, NULL, 0),
(60, 'Hausentwurf:-Architekten-entwerfen-zombiesicheren-Bunker-im-Stil-von-Teslas-Cybertruck', 'Hausentwurf: Architekten entwerfen zombiesicheren Bunker im Stil von Teslas Cybertruck', 'Das passende Haus zum Cybertruck wurde in Moskau entwickelt. Es soll Bomben und Zombiehorden widerstehen und ist ganz nebenbei eine atemberaubende Neuinterpretation des Atriumhauses.', 'Das passende Haus zum Cybertruck wurde in Moskau entwickelt. Es soll Bomben und Zombiehorden widerstehen und ist ganz nebenbei eine atemberaubende Neuinterpretation des Atriumhauses.Offenbar hat der futuristischen Cyber-Tuck ein russisches Architektur-Büro inspiriert, das passende Haus für das Auto zu entwerfen. Als der Chefarchitekt Alex Wizhevsky von Modern House Architecture & Design die Präsentation von Elon Musks Cybertruck sah, fragte er sich, was für eine Person solch einen Panzerwagen fahren würde und welches Haus wohl zu ihm passen würde.\"Anscheinend wurde das Auto geschaffen, um auch unter extremen Bedingungen zu bestehen. Es scheint mir, dass wir dazu ein gut geschütztes Haus, eine Art Festung, einen Bunker brauchen, in dem man jede Bedrohung sicher überleben kann.\"FS CyberhouseAuch ohne Zombies spannendDie Präsentation schwankt zwischen ernsthaften Elementen eines modernen Atriumhauses und Einflüssen aus der Horror-Reihe \"Resident Evil.\" Mitten in einer baumlosen Steppe gelegen soll die Behausung nicht nur gut aussehen, sondern auch noch Bomben und Zombies widerstehen. Eine launige Anspielung auf die Angst der Superreichen vor Aufständen und Apokalypsen, die sich weltweit im Bau von Kellern und Bunkern manifestiert.Ob die schrägen Wände nun wirklich anstürmende Zombie-Horden abwehren können, sei dahingestellt. Alex Wizhevsky sagte, dass sein Entwurf sowohl vom Tesla-Design als auch vom U-Bootbau inspiriert sei. \"Bei der Entwicklung des CyberHouse haben wir das Prinzip des Baus moderner Atom-U-Boote zugrunde gelegt, die aus mehreren Schutzhüllen bestehen\", sagte Wizhevsky. \"Die in unserem Projekt vorgeschlagene mehrschichtige Einhausung bietet maximale Sicherheit vor verschiedenen Katastrophen.\" Das Haus ist auf vollkommene Autonomie ausgelegt. Der Strom wird von Sonnenkollektoren und Windturbinen geliefert. Ziel sei es gewesen, das Überleben der Bewohner für ein Jahr zu garantieren.Industrielle FormspracheTatsächlich gelang dem Büro aus Russland eine interessante Neuinterpretation des Atriumhauses. Nach außen wirkt das Gebäude kühl und abweisend, nach innen öffnet es sich zu einem großzügigen Innenhof. Zwar gibt es noch keinen Auftraggeber für den Bau eines CyberHouse, aber der Architekt geht davon aus, dass mehrere Häuser, die dieser Designsprache folgen, verkauft und gebaut werden. Die Preise beginnen bei umgerechnet 775.000 Euro.Für Modern House Architecture & Design ist die gewagte Präsentation eine Möglichkeit, potenziellen Kunden einen Hinweis für eine zukünftige Architektur zu geben. \"Die Weltarchitektur und jetzt auch die Automobilindustrie, bewegen sich in Richtung Vereinfachung der Formen, maximale Nützlichkeit und Herstellbarkeit\", so Wizhevsky.Lesen Sie auch:Prepper rüsten sich für den Atomkrieg - was wir von ihnen lernen könnenFreiwillig in den Keller - darum wühlen sich die Superreichen in die Tiefe', 'https://image.stern.de/9089978/t/A9/v3/w1440/r1.7778/-/cyb--1-.jpg', NULL, 'https://www.stern.de/digital/technik/architekten-entwerfen-zombiesicheren-bunker-im-stil-von-teslas-cybertruck-9089954.html?utm_campaign=alle&utm_medium=rss-feed&utm_source=standard', '2022-02-12 02:29:00', 'germany', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 2, 'Cybertruck;Bunker;Moskau;Architektur;Auto;Fahrzeug;1970er;Elon Musk;Neuinterpretation', NULL, 0),
(61, 'Racisme-et-discriminations:-l\'envers-du-decor-de-l\'usine-californienne-de-Tesla', 'Racisme et discriminations: l\'envers du décor de l\'usine californienne de Tesla', 'Les prouesses économiques et technologiques de Tesla ont longtemps occulté les critiques contre son fantasque patron Elon Musk et les plaintes de certains employés. Mais des accusations de \"ségrégation raciale\" et de harcèlement sexuel sur son site californien jettent l\'opprobre sur l\'entreprise automobile la plus valorisée en Bourse.', NULL, 'https://fyooyzbm.filerobot.com/v7/tesla+spider+illustration+DR+987678T7Y98OU90-oKVFHHZA.jpg?vh=387fe4&ci_seal=e420f8e656&p=medium&v2&gravity=auto', NULL, 'https://www.varmatin.com/justice/racisme-et-discriminations-lenvers-du-decor-de-lusine-californienne-de-tesla-746035', '2022-02-12 02:01:00', 'france', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 2, NULL, NULL, 0),
(62, 'Tesla-says-its-new-hypercar-will-be-able-to-fly', 'Tesla says its new hypercar will be able to fly', 'Tesla is actively working on the Roadster hypercar, which it unveiled in 2017 but repeatedly delayed Read Full Article at RT.com', 'The chief designer says the Roadster will include SpaceX technology Tesla Chief Designer Franz von Holzhausen gave a long-anticipated update on the electric carmaker’s Roadster hypercar on the Spike Car Radio podcast on Thursday. According to von Holzhausen, the company is “feverishly” working on the vehicle, which will be an “exciting flying machine.” “We are working on the Roadster. I wish we were working faster, but I also wanted to say that, in the time we have been developing it, we have also been learning a lot… All those experiences will, you know, make their way back into a much better Roadster than had we launched right after we debuted it. No products can come fast enough from us for the public, but rest assured we are working on it feverishly,” the designer said. According to him, the highly anticipated hypercar will have an improved (with no further details given) version of Tesla’s new tri-motor powertrain launched in the updated Tesla Model S and Model X last year. And much more. Read more Elon Musk reveals Tesla’s top priority, and it is not cars “It will be an amazing, exciting flying machine with the SpaceX package,” von Holzhausen stated. Tesla CEO Elon Musk announced that the carmaker plans to add a “SpaceX package” to the Roadster, but the designer has now confirmed these plans. The ‘package’ refers to cold air rocket thrusters around the vehicle which are aimed at boosting performance. According to Musk, the technology will allow the Roadster to accelerate from 0 to 100kph in 1.1 seconds, and even allow it to fly, albeit briefly, as the CEO bragged on Twitter. The vehicle will also have a range of nearly 1,000km on one charge. However, the new generation of the Roadster is one of Tesla’s most delayed programs. First unveiled in 2017, it was scheduled to come to the market in 2020. The carmaker delayed the program on more than one occasion, with Musk stressing that the Roadster was not a priority for Tesla. This will actually be able to fly very briefly. I always laughed at flying cars & now making one. Fate 🖤 irony haha.— Elon Musk (@elonmusk) May 21, 2021 In 2020, Musk said the hypercar would be delayed until at least 2022 while the company focused on the release of the Tesla Cybertruck, which is also delayed. There has not been any news regarding the Roadster since September 2021, when Musk said the launch would be delayed even further – until at least 2023. The CEO also stated that the hypercar’s arrival will depend entirely on how much “drama” Tesla goes through in 2022, pointing to worries surrounding the lingering semiconductor chip shortage, which has already led to production delays at some Tesla factories. Despite the delays, 2021 was Tesla’s most successful year in its history, with full-year profits reaching $5.5 billion, up from $721 million in 2020, while sales soared 71% to $53.8 billion, compared to $31.5 billion in 2020. Tesla nearly monopolized the American electric car market in 2021, with over 72% of all electric cars sold in the US last quarter made by Tesla. For more stories on economy & finance visit RT\'s business section', 'https://cdni.rt.com/files/2022.02/thumbnail/620668ae203027507d226ea4.jpg', NULL, 'https://www.rt.com/business/549043-tesla-flying-car-spacex/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=RSS', '2022-02-12 01:56:45', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-07 05:13:57', '2023-07-07 05:13:57', 2, NULL, NULL, 0),
