metamask/', '2023-07-07 00:22:20', 'germany', NULL, '2023-07-07 08:18:42', '2023-07-07 08:18:42', 2, 'Altcoin;Blockchain;Crypto;LUKSO blockcain;LUKSO to metamask;metamask;what is LUKSO', NULL, 0),
(1879, 'Bitcoin-Live-News-:-BTC-Price-Will-Surge-Above-dollar37K-by-July-End-If-This-Happens', 'Bitcoin Live News : BTC Price Will Surge Above $37K by July End If This Happens', 'The post Bitcoin Live News : BTC Price Will Surge Above $37K by July End If This Happens appeared first on Coinpedia Fintech News Bitcoin is currently witnessing a decent rise, as the cryptocurrency attempted to maintain its gains from a recent rally. However, it requires additional catalysts to sustain its upward momentum. Last month, Bitcoin’s rally above the crucial $30,000 level was driven by the news of BlackRock and other companies applying for spot Bitcoin exchange-traded funds (ETFs).  …', 'Bitcoin is currently witnessing a decent rise, as the cryptocurrency attempted to maintain its gains from a recent rally. However, it requires additional catalysts to sustain its upward momentum. Last month, Bitcoin’s rally above the crucial $30,000 level was driven by the news of BlackRock and other companies applying for spot Bitcoin exchange-traded funds (ETFs). This development raised expectations of increased participation from retail and institutional investors in the cryptocurrency market. Bitcoin managed to surpass the $31,000 mark, reaching its highest level in 13 months. However, the cryptocurrency later hit a reversal. While Bitcoin is struggling with short-term resistance, Ethereum is experiencing a bearish divergence. According to a new video by Crypto World, Bitcoin, as of the time of writing, is still within a larger multi-month bullish trend. However, a confirmed breakout above a significant resistance level of around $31,000 is required to validate the bullish momentum. To confirm a breakout above $31,000, a weekly candle close above this level is needed. If this occurs, the next target based on Fibonacci extensions would be around $37,000. However, he said that BTC is currently facing rejection from a resistance level near $31,300. Multiple rejections in the past two weeks suggest that this level is significant. Additionally, an area between $30,800 and $31,000 may also act as short-term resistance based on previous highs. On the support side, the range between $29,900 and $30,100 is important, with $30,000 being a critical level. Talking about Ethereum, he said that it is still within a larger multi-month bullish trend. Higher lows and higher highs on the larger time frames indicate the ongoing bullish momentum. However, like Bitcoin, Ethereum is experiencing a bearish divergence in the shorter term, signaling reduced bullish momentum.', NULL, NULL, 'https://coinpedia.org/bitcoin/bitcoin-live-news-btc-price-will-surge-above-37k-by-july-end-if-this-happens/', '2023-07-06 23:53:48', 'united states of america', NULL, '2023-07-07 08:18:42', '2023-07-07 08:18:42', 2, 'Bitcoin;Price Analysis', NULL, 0),
(1880, 'Former-Kraken-CEO-Jesse-Powell\'s-Home-Raided-by-FBI-in-High-Stakes-Investigation', 'Former Kraken CEO Jesse Powell’s Home Raided by FBI in High-Stakes Investigation', 'The post Former Kraken CEO Jesse Powell’s Home Raided by FBI in High-Stakes Investigation appeared first on Coinpedia Fintech News A high-profile cryptocurrency figure finds himself at the center of a gripping investigation as the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) conducts a search of the Los Angeles home belonging to Jesse Powell, the founder of Kraken, a renowned crypto exchange. Here’s a closer look at the unfolding story: Powell a “Mastermind Hacker” or “Innocent Victim”?  …', 'A high-profile cryptocurrency figure finds himself at the center of a gripping investigation as the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) conducts a search of the Los Angeles home belonging to Jesse Powell, the founder of Kraken, a renowned crypto exchange. Here’s a closer look at the unfolding story: The FBI is delving into allegations that Powell hacked and cyber-stalked Verge Center for the Arts, a nonprofit organization that he himself founded. The focus of the investigation centers around claims that Powell interfered with the organization’s computer accounts, effectively blocking access to crucial emails and other communications. Evidently during the search of Powell’s residence in the affluent Brentwood neighborhood of Los Angeles, law enforcement authorities seized various electronic devices. However, no criminal charges have been filed against Powell at this time, the search signals the seriousness of the investigation and the potential ramifications for the crypto entrepreneur. Powell’s attorney, Brandon Fox, has confirmed that his client is under investigation by federal prosecutors in Northern California. However, Fox emphasized that the probe is specifically related to the allegations made by Verge Center for the Arts and does not pertain to Powell’s professional endeavors within the cryptocurrency industry. Fox firmly asserted Powell’s innocence, stating that he “did nothing wrong.” Kraken, the cryptocurrency exchange founded by Powell, sought to distance itself from the investigation, asserting that it is solely focused on the allegations involving Verge Center for the Arts and does not affect the company. Kraken remains one of the major players in the crypto exchange space, but the outcome of the investigation could have implications for the exchange’s reputation and future prospects. Notably, the entire investigation into Powell’s activities adds to the growing legal scrutiny surrounding Kraken. So far the exchange has faced previous allegations, including claims made in a wrongful termination lawsuit filed against the company in 2019. While the lawsuit was settled in 2021, it accused Kraken of earning revenue from accounts in countries under U.S. sanctions and alleged missing customer deposits. This incident comes amidst a period of increased regulatory scrutiny for cryptocurrency exchanges. Kraken’s competitors, including FTX, Coinbase, and Binance, have also faced significant regulatory challenges. The actions taken by authorities highlight their determination to ensure compliance and tackle potential misconduct within the industry. As the investigation unfolds, the crypto community watches with anticipation to see how this development will impact both Jesse Powell’s future and the broader landscape of the cryptocurrency exchange sector.', NULL, NULL, 'https://coinpedia.org/news/former-kraken-ceo-jesse-powells-home-raided-by-fbi-in-high-stakes-investigation/', '2023-07-06 23:41:02', 'united states of america', NULL, '2023-07-07 08:18:42', '2023-07-07 08:18:42', 2, 'News;Crypto news', NULL, 0);
