(2043, 'Plan-to-crack-down-nonrevenue-water-on-course-PS-Rono', 'Plan to crack down nonrevenue water on course - PS Rono', 'He said to effectively manage the NRW to acceptable standards, there was a need to adopt practical measures.', 'The Ministry of Water has launched the non-revenue water management (NRW) standards to be applicable to all water service providers across the country. Principal Secretary in charge of Water and Sanitation Paul Rono said in order for the country to effectively manage the NRW to acceptable standards, there was a need to adopt practical measures. “Our NRW is currently high at 45 percent and we have to bring it down by applying strategies which include speed and quality of repair once a leak has been detected, active leakage control mechanisms, asset management, and pressure management as both short term and long term measures,” said Rono. Speaking during the launch at a Nairobi hotel, the PS termed the initiative as a step in the right direction noting Kenya now joins the few countries in Africa to adopt the standards. He directed the various agencies in the Ministry to comply with the standards in order to bring down NRW to 5 percent within the next three years. Kenya Water Institute (KEWI), he noted, will now be tasked with strengthening the training programs for NRW and providing at least three certified staff to be employed by each of the 88 registered water service providers. The Water Services Regulatory Board (WASREB) on its part will take charge and ensure implementation of the standards as well as come up with a working mechanism within three months. “It is also expected to come up with a drastic review of equipment and technology to be used by the counties through smart meters,” he said. To ensure the utilization of bulk water, Water Regulatory Authority (WRA) is set to monitor the process within one year for compliance. All the Water Services Providers (WSPs), the PS said, will be required to create NRW sections and deploy the best employees with high standards of integrity to manage the unit\'s affairs. “There is an urgent need for all the WSPs to meet and implement the standards and operationalize in order to serve the citizens with water provision as outlined in the Constitution 2010 and Water Act 2016,” he added. The PS at the same time lauded Meru and Nyeri Water companies for managing NRW. The two counties are being supported by JICA which trains the WSPs on the best practices to manage NRW. Present during the event were Water Secretary SAO Alima, Secretary of Administration Stephen Kihara, Nairobi City Water and Sewerage Company CEO Nahashon Muguna, and heads of various agencies.', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.the-star.co.ke/news/realtime/2023-07-07-plan-to-crack-down-nonrevenue-water-on-course-ps-rono/', '2023-07-07 10:02:01', 'kenya', NULL, '2023-07-07 17:00:06', '2023-07-07 17:00:06', 2, NULL, '', 0),
(2044, 'Snl24.com-or-Pitso\'s-Lieutenant:-Egyptians-Are-\'On-Another-Level\'', 'Snl24.com | Pitso\'s Lieutenant: Egyptians Are \'On Another Level\'', 'One of Pitso Mosimane\'s trusted members of his technical team, Musi Matlaba, has opened up on their experience in Egypt with Al Ahly and discusses what he thinks makes those players different from South Africans.', 'One of Pitso Mosimane\'s trusted members of his technical team, Musi Matlaba, has opened up on their experience in Egypt with Al Ahly and discusses what he thinks makes those players different from South Africans. Matlaba has been working with Mosimane from their days at Mamelodi Sundowns as a performance analyst and scout. He had moved with the former Bafana Bafana coach to Al Ahly in September 2020. Mosimane and his team, including the likes of fitness coach, Kabelo Rangoaga, analyst Kyle Solomon (who joined a year later) and Matlaba, won the CAF Champions League twice with the Red Devils, among other titles and moved on to another challenge in Saudi Arabia last season, where they won the Yelo League (First Division) with Al Ahli Saudi that brought that club back to the topflight. Matlaba, who is moving with the Mosimane technical team to United Arab Emirates outfit Al Wahda for the upcoming campaign, has opened up on what they learned with Egyptian players when compared to those in the PSL. \"What we learned with the players, very physical players in Egypt. They literally leave everything on the pitch. I could say in terms of one v ones, passing and moving, not as good as South Africans,\" Matlaba said on YouTube Channel. \"There were times where we were not good on the pitch, the game was not going our way but simply because the players will, they believe \'we have to win, there\'s no other way\', we won matches,\" he said. Matlaba also revealed that the players at the Red Devils were initially not open to the way they do things but once they committed themselves, they implemented new methods quicker than imagined. \"The players weren\'t open to the way we do things at the beginning because usually that time it was just show up to the game and play,\" he said. \"So the players were like, \'Ah but this feels like school\'. It is school, it is football school,\" he continued. \"But the players in Egypt made it easy to work with. We thought things that would take four, five, six months to implement, literally in the first game, three, four days they were doing it. \"And we were like, \'This is another level\',\" he added. You must be to read and post comments.', 'https://scripts.24.co.za/img/sites/soccerladuma24.png', NULL, 'https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/Local/SA-Players-Abroad/pitso-mosimanes-lieutenant-egyptian-players-on-another-level-compared-to-south-africans-20230708', '2023-07-08 05:13:08', 'south africa', NULL, '2023-07-08 11:30:01', '2023-07-08 11:30:01', 7, NULL, '', 0),
(2045, 'Snl24.com-or-Swallows-Confirm-Third-2324-Signing', 'Snl24.com | Swallows Confirm Third 23/24 Signing', 'Swallows FC have continued to bolster their squad for the new season with the arrival of third signing.', 'Swallows FC have continued to bolster their squad for the new season with the arrival of third signing. The Soweto giants have brought in another player from Uthongathi following the arrival of defender Falakhe Tshanini. The 27-year-old was a regular for Uthongathi in the Motsepe Foundation Championship last season, having racked up 27 appearances, with 24 coming as a starter. The Dube Birds have already confirmed the arrivals of midfielders Lantshene Phalane and Victor Bakah on Friday.', 'https://scripts.24.co.za/img/sites/soccerladuma24.png', NULL, 'https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/Local/Premiership/Swallows-FC/swallows-announce-third-signing-for-the-20232024-season-20230708', '2023-07-08 05:13:08', 'south africa', NULL, '2023-07-08 11:30:01', '2023-07-08 11:30:01', 7, NULL, '', 0),
(2046, 'News24.com-or-Horror-Cape-Town-crash:-Death-toll-rises-to-6-as-another-pupil-dies-in-hospital', 'News24.com | Horror Cape Town crash: Death toll rises to 6 as another pupil dies in hospital', 'A sixth pupil involved in a fatal crash along AZ Berman Drive in Mitchells Plain at the end of May, has died in hospital.', 'A sixth pupil involved in a fatal crash along AZ Berman Drive in Mitchells Plain at the end of May, has died in hospital. Five other schoolchildren, all from Khayelitsha, died at the scene of the crash in Beacon Valley on 30 May, while on their way to school. The pupils - aged between seven and 13 - were from Ridgeville Primary, Harvester Primary, Duneside Primary, Highlands Primary and Westpoort Primary, News24 previously reported. After the accident, two pupils were rushed to a nearby hospita l for treatment. One of them has now died, said Western Cape Education MEC David Maynier. \"We have been informed that a Lentegeur High School learner who was seriously injured in a traffic collision in Mitchells Plain at the end of May has sadly passed away in hospital. The collision had already claimed the lives of five young learners, and it is a great tragedy that a sixth has now been added,\" he said. Maynier added that the district office was providing support to pupils and loved ones. READ | 5 pupils killed in horror Cape Town crash: \'The worst news any parent can receive\' \"We offer our deepest condolences to his family, friends and school at this very difficult time,\" he said. At the time of the accident, bystanders said a white Toyota Hilux bakkie, which the children were travelling in, had hit the pavement at the traffic island, before smashing into the traffic light. The pupils were flung from the bakkie. The driver, 56-year-old Mninkhaya Mvuli, has since been arrested and charged with five counts of culpable homicide and reckless driving.', 'https://scripts.24.co.za/img/sites/news24.png', NULL, 'https://www.news24.com/news24/SouthAfrica/News/horror-cape-town-crash-death-toll-rises-to-6-as-another-pupil-dies-in-hospital-20230708', '2023-07-08 05:07:25', 'south africa', NULL, '2023-07-08 11:30:01', '2023-07-08 11:30:01', 2, NULL, '', 0),
(2047, 'Terry-To-Return-To-Chelsea-Academy', 'Terry To Return To Chelsea Academy', 'Former Chelsea captain John Terry announced his return to the academy of the Premier League club just less than a month after his stint with Leicester City, where he was the assistant manager. The 42-year-old former England skipper returned to Chelsea in a coaching consultancy role in 2022 before joining Dean Smith’s coaching staff at… Read More »Terry To Return To Chelsea Academy', 'Former Chelsea captain John Terry announced his return to the academy of the Premier League club just less than a month after his stint with Leicester City, where he was the assistant manager. The 42-year-old former England skipper returned to Chelsea in a coaching consultancy role in 2022 before joining Dean Smith’s coaching staff at Leicester in April this year. Terry’s contract at Leicester was not renewed following the side’s relegation from the English top flight. “I’m delighted to be back Home working in the academy and continuing my role at the club,” Terry, who started his coaching career in 2018 as an assistant manager at Aston Villa, said in an Instagram post. The former defender and five-time Premier League champion won every major trophy during his 19-year stint at Stamford Bridge, making him Chelsea’s most successful captain. Reuters', NULL, NULL, 'https://iafrica.com/terry-to-return-to-chelsea-academy/', '2023-07-08 05:02:20', 'south africa', NULL, '2023-07-08 11:30:01', '2023-07-08 11:30:01', 2, 'SPORT;Chelsea;football;john terry;soccer', '', 0),
