(2077, 'Janhvi-Kapoor-Says-Visit-To-Auschwitz-During-Bawaal-Shoot-Left-A-Long-Lasting-Impression-On-Her', 'Janhvi Kapoor Says Visit To Auschwitz During Bawaal Shoot Left A Long-Lasting Impression On Her', 'The upcoming Janhvi Kapoor and Varun Dhawan-starrer film Bawaal has been shot in several picturesque locations.', 'The upcoming Janhvi Kapoor and Varun Dhawan-starrer film Bawaal has been shot in several picturesque locations. However, while shooting in Poland, a visit to Auschwitz had a long lasting impact on Janhvi. Auschwitz concentration camp was a complex of over 40 concentration and extermination camps operated by Nazi Germany in occupied Poland during World War II and the Holocaust. Bawaal Trailer: Varun Dhawan and Janhvi Kapoor’s Love Saga Has To Pass Through a War of Its Own in Nitesh Tiwari’s Upcoming Film (Watch Video) . Bawaal , which has been directed by acclaimed filmmaker Nitesh Tiwari, has glimpses of World War 2 and the concentration camp. Talking about what location is the most loved by Janhvi, she said: \"I think Amsterdam for me because I fell in love with the city and as a team we spent a lot of time in that city as well but when we were in Poland we actually went to visit Auschwitz, which was a very moving experience.\" She added: \"It taught us a lot about the gravity of what we were making and speaking about. So that left a long lasting impression on me and Varun both.\" Produced by Sajid Nadiadwala\'s Nadiadwala Grandson Entertainment in collaboration with Ashwiny Iyer Tiwari and Nitesh Tiwari\'s Earthsky Pictures, Bawaal will have its global premiere on Prime Video on July 21. (The above story first appeared on LatestLY on Jul 09, 2023 07:59 PM IST. For more news and updates on politics, world, sports, entertainment and lifestyle, log on to our website latestly.com ).', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.latestly.com/entertainment/bollywood/janhvi-kapoor-says-visit-to-auschwitz-during-bawaal-shoot-left-a-long-lasting-impression-on-her-5253813.html', '2023-07-09 08:59:16', 'india', NULL, '2023-07-09 15:30:02', '2023-07-09 15:30:02', 5, NULL, '', 0),
(2078, 'Kylie-Jenner-is-slammed-by-fans-for-\'flaunting-her-wealth\'-in-a-now-deleted-racy-TikTok', 'Kylie Jenner is slammed by fans for \'flaunting her wealth\' in a now deleted racy TikTok', 'Kylie Jenner has been slammed by fans for \'showing off her wealth\' in a new racy TikTok video which she posted - and then deleted.', 'Kylie Jenner is slammed for \'flaunting her wealth\' as she shows off a $300k Birkin bag in now deleted TikTok post By Bethan Edwards For Mailonline Published: 06:51 EDT, 9 July 2023 | Updated: 10:55 EDT, 9 July 2023 e-mail 120 shares 207 View comments Kylie Jenner has been slammed by fans for \'showing off her wealth\' in a new racy TikTok video which she posted - and then deleted. The Kardashians star, 25, dressed in a slinky, silk halter-neck dress which she teamed with a designer Faubourg Birkin bag, which she was gifted for her 25th birthday. In the video she uploaded on Thursday, she showed off the bag which is designed to look like the Hermes flagship store and is said to be valued at nearly $300,000. Fans of the makeup mogul have now called her out for flaunting her wealth as she showed off the designer accessory which they claimed \'looked horrible with her outfit\'. Taking to a Reddit chatroom, one said: \'It looks horrible with that outfit!! Her outfit has cool tones and that bag has a warm beige plus white color!\' Oh dear: Kylie Jenner has been slammed by fans for \'showing off her wealth\' in a new racy TikTok video which she posted - and then deleted \'She wears it to show off her wealth\': The Kardashians star, 25, dressed in a slinky, silk halter-neck dress which she teamed with a designer Faubourg Birkin bag, which is valued at nearly $300,000 Another added: \'She wears it to show off her wealth, but a woman with class picks a bag that compliments her outfit instead.\' While a third noted the bag looked familiar: \'Crystal Minkoff from RHOBH has the same Birkin, and they talked about how much it is on an episode. All the housewives were foaming at the mouth for it lol.\' The video started with the makeup mogul - who shared snaps of her kids on Instagram on Thursday - dressed in light grey, slightly sheer bra and boxer shorts. The Hulu star leaned toward the camera and revealed that she had spilled water on her bra. The mom of two shook her head and picked up a silvery grey silk dress. The Keeping Up with the Kardashians alum tied the two slim straps of the dress behind her neck and then pulled on a string on the back of the dress to fit it to her figure and create a ruching effect. She smoothed the dress over her curves and added strappy white heels to the look. As she walked towards the camera, it became obvious that she had ditched her bra as her nipples were visible beneath the fabric of her dress. Not happy: Fans of the makeup mogul have now called her out for flaunting her wealth as she showed off the designer accessory which they claimed \'looked horrible with her outfit\' She posed holding a cute white handbag which showed off her light pink manicure and the rings she wore on her fingers. The SZA song Love Galore played in the background of the TikTok. Travis Scott was featured on the original version of the song. The couple split last year for the final time. They first got together in 2017 and broke up in 2019. They reconciled a few times before their most recent split. Fans have speculated that the couple may be getting back together, especially since she keeps wearing rings on her wedding ring finger . But a source told TMZ that they are united as co-parents to daughter Stormi, 5, and son Aire, 17 months and that their most recent break \'feels more permanent.\' The brunette beauty has been romancing actor Timothee Chalamet , 27, since April. The Call Me By Your Name actor and Kylie were spotted on a late night taco date and at an art show in Santa Monica. An eyewitness told DailyMail.com that Chalamet left the event, and was \'looking around anxiously\' while \'texting constantly on his phone.\' Not long later Jenner pulled up and he hopped into the backseat with her and her security detail, and they drove off. Share or comment on this article: Kylie Jenner is slammed by fans for \'flaunting her wealth\' in a now deleted racy TikTok e-mail 120 shares Add comment', 'https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2023/07/09/09/73010627-0-image-m-10_1688893064980.jpg', NULL, 'https://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-12279709/Kylie-Jenner-slammed-fans-flaunting-wealth-deleted-racy-TikTok.html?ns_mchannel=rss&ns_campaign=1490&ito=1490', '2023-07-09 08:57:48', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-09 15:30:02', '2023-07-09 15:30:02', 5, NULL, '', 0),
(2079, 'Brad-Pitt-dons-a-racer\'s-jumpsuit-as-he-joins-celebs-at-F1-British-Grand-Prix-at-Silverstone', 'Brad Pitt dons a racer\'s jumpsuit as he joins celebs at F1 British Grand Prix at Silverstone', 'The actor, 59, looked the part as he donned a white fire suit for the occasion and mingled with the other celebrity spectators.', 'Brad Pitt dons a racer\'s jumpsuit as he joins celebrity spectators at the British Grand Prix at Silverstone ahead of filming upcoming F1 movie Apex By Geraint Llewellyn For Mailonline Published: 15:26, 9 July 2023 | Updated: 15:54, 9 July 2023 e-mail View comments Brad Pitt arrived at the Formula 1 Grand Prix in Silverstone in character as fictional race car driver Sonny Hayes from his new movie Apex on Saturday. The actor, 59, looked the part as he donned a white fire suit for the occasion and mingled with the other celebrity spectators to film scenes ahead of the big race. His suit sported the logos of his characters sponsors and he completed the look with a pair of stylish aviator shades. Brad slicked his brunette locks into a quiff as he strutted his stuff amongst the parked cars ahead of the much anticipated British Formula 1 race. Meanwhile Florence Pugh turned heads as she made a quirky appearance on the track. Ready to race: Brad Pitt, 59, arrived at the Formula 1 in Silverstone in character as fictional race car driver Sonny Hayes from his new movie Apex on Saturday Racer: The actor looked the part as he donned a white fire suit for the occasion and mingled with the other celebrity spectators as he filmed scenes ahead of the big race The actress, 27, sported super short hair that was dyed pink as she racing legend Sir Jackie Stewart, 84. Florence wore a denim jacket adorned with red graffiti and matching trousers as she was given a VIP tour ahead of the race. She sported a flawless make-up look with pillar box red lipstick and a statement making gold piercing in her nose. Elsewhere Geri Horner opted for a white denim jumpsuit as 