(2083, 'F1-British-Grand-Prix-2023-LIVE!-Race-stream-and-latest-updates-as-Max-Verstappen-leads-Lando-Norris', 'F1 British Grand Prix 2023 LIVE! Race stream and latest updates as Max Verstappen leads Lando Norris', 'British Grand Prix LIVE!', 'LIVE! The roadshow rolls back into this weekend for one of the signature staple events on the annual racing calendar. Hundreds of thousands of car fanatics have descended upon this famous corner of Northamptonshire, where there is even more glitz and glamour than usual with a distinct Hollywood flavour as Brad Pitt films scenes from his highly-anticipated upcoming film. On the track, is looking to win the British Grand Prix for the first time at an unhappy hunting ground for Red Bull as the dominant reigning world champion claimed yet another pole position in search of a sixth successive race victory this afternoon. Behind him it’s Britain’s Lando Norris and Oscar Piastri, with McLaren having produced a dream finish to qualifying on Saturday as their new upgrades take quick effect. Lewis Hamilton is an eight-time winner of his home race but faces a hugely difficult task today from seventh on the grid, one spot behind Mercedes team-mate and fellow Briton George Russell. Race organisers will be hoping to avoid any potentially dangerous environmental protests this afternoon after Just Stop Oil continued their campaign at Wimbledon. Follow all the drama from the British Grand Prix live below, with Matt Majendie reporting from Silverstone. Lap 22: The dream could be over for Norris, with Verstappen leading by five seconds. How have McLaren found this improved pace at their homw race? Some have been suggesting their upgrades are a copycat of the Red Bull. But team boss Andrea Stella said such a comparison is unfair. Saying that, their improved pace has been enough for Mercedes to readily admitted that they might change tack once more again and be more Red Bull-esque with their sidepods. Whatever the case, they’re currently off the McLaren’s race pace. Lap 14: “The wind is making it difficult to drive at the moment.” Lando Norris still trails, with Piastri just behind him. Lap 11: Red Bull team radio suggests some light rain will arrive in 2-3 minutes and last for around 3-4 minutes. Lap 10: A real shame for Ocon, who suffered front wing damage early on and has been forced to retire. Ah, we have the 2023 season familiarity after all now. Verstappen gets past Norris and you hear a slight deflation from those inside Silverstone. He’s now a second clear and, unless there’s a reliability issue or else the rain comes down (it’s possible as it’s been reported nearby), you’d think it’s win No8 on the cards for the Dutchman. Interestingly, he’s never won the British Grand Prix before although did win the second of two Silverstone races in Covid times, the so called 70th Anniversary Race. Lap 7: Hasn’t been a great start for Lewis Hamilton after drifting wide at the start but he’s up ahead of Fernando Alonso into seventh. Norris and Piastri are going to attack leader Verstappen together. Lap 5: Verstappen moves inside Norris with absolute ease to reclaim top spot. Lap 4: Ominous signs as Verstappen cuts Norris’s lead down to half a second. The mighty Red Bull is edging closer and, with DRS enabled, this could be huge. Lapo 3: With two laps down, DRS is now in play.', 'https://static.standard.co.uk/2023/07/09/15/newFile-2.jpg?width=1200&auto=webp', NULL, 'https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/formula-one/f1-british-grand-prix-2023-live-stream-race-updates-latest-news-result-today-b1093164.html', '2023-07-09 08:50:31', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-09 15:30:02', '2023-07-09 15:30:02', 2, 'F1;Sport', '', 0),
(2084, 'Ashes-2023-LIVE-updates:-England-claim-win-at-Headingley-Ashes-alive-at-2-1-heading-to-Old-Trafford', 'Ashes 2023 LIVE updates: England claim win at Headingley, Ashes alive at 2-1 heading to Old Trafford', 'England have won the third Test at Headingley with three wickets to spare. The Ashes remain alive at 2-1 heading to Old Trafford in Manchester.', 'Key posts 11.18pm Match report 10.57pm Wood named player of the match 10.42pm Scorecard summary 10.39pm England win 10.23pm Brook OUT! 10.01pm Partnership moves to 40 9.19pm Bairstow OUT! 9.07pm Stokes OUT! Hide key posts Posts area Latest 1 of 8 Oldest Latest posts Latest posts 11.18pm Match report By Malcolm Conn Fast bowling hero Mark Wood became England’s batting hero as they Bazballed their way to a heart-stopping victory in the third Test at Headingley, keeping the series alive and robbing the chance for Australia to claim their first series victory in England for 22 years. Set 251 for victory, England won by three wickets midway through the fourth day, leaving the series at 2-1 with two Tests to play. Mark Wood and Chris Woakes leave the field after guiding England to victory. Credit: Getty Images Still needing 21 for victory when he can to the crease, Wood smote a six over fine leg and a four through the covers on the way to an unbeaten 16 from just eight balls. Wood was player of the match for his first innings 5-34 and the difference between the teams after missing the first two Tests recovering from injury. READ MORE HERE 11.16pm Changes for the fourth Test? What will the Australian team look like for the next Test? You’d be safe to assume Scott Boland will be replaced with Josh Hazelwood. Does Mitch Marsh lose his spot to Cameron Green? Does Green sit out another Test? Or could Green come in for David Warner? David Warner reacts after being dismissed by Stuart Broad again. Credit: Getty Images Or does Marcus Harris get another look in the side? And what about Todd Murphy? Out of 50 overs, he bowled just two in the final innings. Could Australia play Michael Neser too? This would be a unique looking XI, let us know in the comments what you think: Usman Khawaja, Mitch Marsh, Marnus Labuschagne, Steve Smith, Travis Head, Cameron Green, Alex Carey, Mitch Starc, Pat Cummins, Michael Neser, Josh Hazelwood. 11.01pm Ashes player ratings: All Aussies rated out of 10 By Daniel Brettig Three players get 9/10 ratings, two get just 4/10 and one just 3/10. The Age’s chief cricket writer Dan Brettig rates the performances of Australia’s XI in the third Test at Headingley. Read the ratings here Mitch Starc. Credit: Reuters Advertisement 10.57pm Wood named player of the match Could have been three or four options for man of the match, but Mark Wood is the right call. He took 5-34 off 11.4 overs in the first innings, including a chaotic spell late in Australia’s first innings where the tourists lost 6-23. In Australia’s second innings, he took 2-66. He also hit a handy 24 in England’s first innings and 16 not out in the second dig. 10.48pm Reaction to Australia’s loss 10.42pm Scorecard summary First innings: AUS 263 (Marsh 118, Wood 5-34) Second innings: ENG 237 (Stokes 80, Cummins 6-91) Third innings: AUS 224 (Head 77, Broad 3-45) Fourth innings: ENG 7-254 (Brook 75, Starc 5-78) Advertisement 10.39pm England win A boundary seals the victory. England have taken the Ashes scoreline to 2-1, heading to Old Trafford. England win by three wickets at Headingley. 10.36pm Carey drops Wood A chance goes down. Starc bowls short to Wood, who slashes again, and it goes high over Carey’s head. Scotty Boland at fly slip probably could have run in and taken that catch. But Carey ran back and dived, outstretched, and put it down. Now Woakes has worked Starc away for a single. England need two to win. 10.34pm Now just four to win Another one at the stumps, and Wood knocks it to deep point for two runs. Four to win for England. Advertisement 10.34pm Wood drives Starc for four Mitch Starc around the wicket, field set for the short ball, but Starc goes full at the stumps and Wood hits him for four. England need seven runs to win. And now a wide has been paid against Starc. England now need six to win. Latest 1 of 8 Oldest Latest Oldest Most Viewed in Sport Loading', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.watoday.com.au/sport/cricket/ashes-2023-live-updates-england-need-224-to-win-third-test-australia-need-10-wickets-to-win-series-20230709-p5dmxc.html?ref=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_source=rss_sport', '2023-07-09 09:31:30', 'australia', NULL, '2023-07-09 16:00:02', '2023-07-09 16:00:02', 7, NULL, '', 0),
(2085, 'Ashes-player-ratings:-How-Australia-performed-in-the-Headingley-Test', 'Ashes player ratings: How Australia performed in the Headingley Test', 'We run the rule over the Australian side after their loss to England in the third Test.', 'Travis Head 9/10 Supported Mitch Marsh in the innings that kept Australia in the game after losing the toss on day one, and then carved out a courageous 77 with the tail in the second to give them something to bowl at. Head’s series has been subdued at times, simply by nature of the concerted short ball attack he has faced, but at Lord’s and Headingley he has been able to problem-solve and still damage England with vital runs. At 73, Head’s series strike rate is up with the fastest for the series in spite of those tactics. Travis Head (left) celebrates his 50. Credit: Reuters Mitchell Marsh 9/10 Called up because Cam Green had a slight hamstring strain, Marsh made it count with one of the great Ashes innings on day one, a solo 118 including a century in a session - the first Australian to do that in England since Stan McCabe in 1938. Played sublimely in the second innings too until he was fractionally too late choosing to leave a ball from Chris Woakes. Bowled more than handily also, picking up the key wicket of Zak Crawley in each innings after the England opener had made a start. Loading Mitchell Starc 9/10 Fast, straight and a consistent threat all match. Starc’s domination of Jonny Bairstow continued by getting him in each innings, while the wickets of Ben Duckett, Moeen Ali and Stokes (albeit fortuitously glancing into Alex Carey’s gloves) put Australia right in the contest on the final day. Has developed all the skills he needs to succeed in England on his fourth Ashes tour, and used them to great effect here. Mitchell Starc after claiming the wicket of Jonny Bairstow in the second innings. Credit: Reuters Loading', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.watoday.com.au/sport/cricket/ashes-player-ratings-how-australia-performed-in-the-headingley-test-20230709-p5dmxr.html?ref=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_source=rss_sport', '2023-07-09 09:22:58', 'australia', NULL, '2023-07-09 16:00:02', '2023-07-09 16:00:02', 7, NULL, '', 0),
