(2292, 'Thornhill:-Southampton-boy-stabbed-on-Linacre-Road', 'Thornhill: Southampton boy stabbed on Linacre Road', 'A 14-year-old boy has been stabbed in the back in Thornhill, Southampton.', 'A TEENAGE boy has been rushed to hospital after he was stabbed in the back in a Southampton neighbourhood. Police rushed to Linacre Road in Thornhill just after 7pm last night after a 14-year-old was stabbed. He was taken to hospital and officers have implemented stop and search powers. The emergency powers, which were put in place at 8.40pm last night, will run until 8.40pm tonight, Monday, July 10. A map of the stop and search area in Thornhill. (Image: Hampshire Constabulary) It gives police the power to stop and search anyone in a designated location, without the restrictions of normal stop and search. The powers will be in place around the majority of the Thornhill and Sholing area. Officers will be carrying out patrols across the local area and will be able to stop and search anyone while the powers are in use. Anyone with information about this incident should call 101 using reference number 44230275652 We want our comments to be a lively and valuable part of our community - a place where readers can debate and engage with the most important local issues. The ability to comment on our stories is a privilege, not a right, however, and that privilege may be withdrawn if it is abused or misused. Please report any comments that break our rules. Comments are closed on this article', 'https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/resources/images/16980500/', NULL, 'https://www.dailyecho.co.uk/news/23644047.thornhill-southampton-boy-stabbed-linacre-road/?ref=rss', '2023-07-10 00:54:07', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-10 07:30:01', '2023-07-10 07:30:01', 2, NULL, '', 0),
