(3341, 'Mercedes-poised-to-switch-full-focus-to-2024-F1-car-and-abandon-\"Diva-2.0\"', 'Mercedes poised to switch full focus to 2024 F1 car and abandon “Diva 2.0”', 'The German manufacturer was outgunned by McLaren at the British Grand Prix in the battle behind Red Bull, as Lewis Hamilton did not have the pace to overhaul Lando Norris for second spot.A major overhaul of the W14 introduced at the Monaco Grand Prix had initially appeared to give the squad the uptick in form it felt it needed to fight for wins, but it has failed to build on that early ...Keep reading', 'The German manufacturer was outgunned by McLaren at the British Grand Prix in the battle behind Red Bull, as Lewis Hamilton did not have the pace to overhaul Lando Norris for second spot . A major overhaul of the W14 introduced at the Monaco Grand Prix had initially appeared to give the squad the uptick in form it felt it needed to fight for wins, but it has failed to build on that early promise. And as it appears stuck in the chasing pack behind Red Bull, there is a growing acceptance that the team cannot make the changes it wants with the W14 that it feels is essential to close down the deficit to the front. That is why team boss Toto Wolff thinks the moment is nearing where Mercedes will have to accept that its future is better set throwing all its resources towards what is expected to be a fundamental redesign for next season. Asked by Autosport at what point that decision will be made, Wolff said “I think pretty soon. We have no choice. “P2 or P3 fundamentally doesn\'t impact me and the team. It\'s about coming back and being able to win a world championship in that respect. That\'s not going to happen this year. “So we need to set our eyes to next year and then, at all the races to come, learn and develop, and make sure that we can carry that forward into next year. “But, having said that, the regulations are the same. So it\'s not that you\'re not learning nothing by continuing this car. It\'s a balance that we have to strike right.” George Russell, Mercedes F1 W14 Photo by: Steve Etherington / Motorsport Images While McLaren’s amazing step forward this season has highlighted the potential for big gains, Mercedes does not see scope for it to do a similar step soon. Wolff said that limitations imposed by the cost cap, plus wind tunnel restrictions, leave his outfit only able to bring some minor improvements over the remainder of the campaign. “I think we are restricted by the cost cap and by the relative less amount in wind tunnel and CFD time that McLaren was able to have,” he explained. Read Also: Verstappen: Changing F1 order behind Red Bull \"very confusing\" McLaren explains reason behind F1 British GP hard tyre call for Norris F1 car inconsistency behind Ferrari struggles in British GP \"They finished further back in the championship and they were like fifth or sixth mid-year. So they carried over that more wind tunnel time allocation. And that\'s why it\'s kind of difficult. “Do I believe that we have upgrades in there that are going to fundamentally change the car? I don\'t believe so. But we have a few small steps that are to come. And you can see that if you find the tenth or two or three, it puts you in a different position on the grid.” Mercedes’ admission that thoughts will soon have to shift to 2024 come after a British GP weekend where the team had hoped to perform much better, as Silverstone’s high-speed swoops should have suited the car perfectly. Instead, it was McLaren that shone at the track. Toto Wolff, Team Principal and CEO, Mercedes-AMG Photo by: Michael Potts / Motorsport Images Wolff still believes that the squad can pull together a win to beat Verstappen at some point, but it is not going to be easy – especially as he thinks the current car is worse for his drivers than the infamous W08 from 2017 that earned the ‘Diva’ nickname. Wolff added: “I thought that Silverstone based on our historic performances was the best shot, but it wasn\'t. So maybe there\'s another track where we have the best shot because the characteristics of the car have changed. “I always believe that we can beat Max, we have a good group of people, and the best drivers. “We just have to give them a car that is more predictable, and not the Diva 2.0, plus much more complicated than the first one.” shares comments', 'https://cdn-7.motorsport.com/images/amp/YEQgnG5Y/s6/lewis-hamilton-mercedes-f1-w14.jpg', NULL, 'https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/mercedes-poised-to-switch-full-focus-to-2024-f1-car-and-abandon-diva-20/10494203/?utm_source=RSS&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=RSS-ALL&utm_term=News&utm_content=uk', '2023-07-10 02:58:39', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-10 09:30:01', '2023-07-10 09:30:01', 7, NULL, '', 0),
(3342, 'Az-megvan-mikor-egy-csorda-szedelgo-strucc-lekoborol-a-benzinkutra-edessegert-Struccfarmon-neveltek-a-marihuanat-Hodmezovasarhelyen', 'Az megvan, mikor egy csorda szédelgő strucc lekóborol a benzinkútra édességért? - Struccfarmon nevelték a marihuánát Hódmezővásárhelyen', 'Persze nem történt semmi ilyesmi, a struccok nem ostobák és nem legelték le a kifutójuk mellett nevel marihuánaültetvényt, maradtak a kifutójukban, de azért a történet így is szokatlan. Mármint az, hogy a hódmezővásárhelyi struccfarmról kiderüljön, hogy valójában drogültetvény. A termesztők ellen most emeltek vádat, ma közölte az ügyészség.', 'Vádat emeltek tehát két férfi és egyikük élettársa ellen, akik Hódmezővásárhelyen alakítottak ki indiaikender-ültetvényt, ahol több mint ezerhatszáz növényt neveltek ‒ tájékoztatott hétfőn az ügyészség. A letartóztatásban lévő három embert jelentős mennyiségű kábítószer társtettességben elkövetett kereskedelmével vádolják. A nő tulajdonában álló telek szabadtéri részén, illetve erre speciálisan kialakított beltéri helyiségekben a pár és társuk a vádirat szerint indiaikender-ültetvényt alakított ki. A növényeket a pár gondozta, beérésüket követően azokat betakarították, szárították, majd a kiadagolt kábítószert társuk értékesítette. A tanyán tavaly június 8-án a nyomozók 1630 tő indiai kendert, hat kiló, már szárítás alatt álló ágvégződést, valamint az értékesítéshez szükséges egyéb eszközöket foglalt le. A lefoglalt kábítószer hatóanyag-tartalma több mint tizenhatszorosa a jelentős mennyiség alsó határának. A felderítésről szóló korábbi, rendőrségi közlemény szerint a tanyán ‒ feltehetően álcázásként ‒ struccfarm működött, ahol közvetlenül a futómadarak kifutója mellett alakították ki az indiaikender-ültetvényt.', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.blikk.hu/aktualis/krimi/strucc-hodmezovasarhely-fu/cdfjsvp', '2023-07-10 02:57:39', 'hungary', NULL, '2023-07-10 09:30:01', '2023-07-10 09:30:01', 2, 'Aktuális', '', 0),
(3343, 'DSS-Never-Raided-CCB-Offices-For-Documents-Against-Tinubu-Spokesperson', 'DSS Never Raided CCB Offices For Documents Against Tinubu – Spokesperson', 'The Code of Conduct Bureau (CCB) has denied reports that the Department of State Services, DSS, raided its offices to cart away incriminating documents on President Bola Tinubu. The agency,… The post DSS Never Raided CCB Offices For Documents Against Tinubu – Spokesperson first appeared on Royal Times of Nigeria..', 'The Code of Conduct Bureau (CCB) has denied reports that the Department of State Services, DSS, raided its offices to cart away incriminating documents on President Bola Tinubu. The agency, in a statement by Daniel Okafor, Director of Education and Advocacy Services, said the claim was false. “The attention of the Code of Conduct Bureau has been drawn to a publication on Friday 7th July, 2023, in Sahara Reporters, claiming that the DSS raided offices of anti-corruption agencies, specifically the CCB, ICPC and EFCC, and carted away documents affecting President Bola Ahmed Tinubu and his associates”, it reads. Join our twitter community : Follow @royaltimesng Code of Conduct Bureau Daniel Okafor Department of State Services President Bola Tinubu', NULL, NULL, 'https://royaltimes.net/dss-never-raided-ccb-offices-for-documents-against-tinubu-spokesperson/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=dss-never-raided-ccb-offices-for-documents-against-tinubu-spokesperson', '2023-07-10 02:56:22', 'nigeria', NULL, '2023-07-10 09:30:01', '2023-07-10 09:30:01', 2, 'News;Code of Conduct Bureau;Daniel Okafor;Department of State Services;President Bola Tinubu', '', 0),
(3344, 'Malta-has-a-\'strong-case\'-to-continue-to-allow-spring-hunting-Clint-Camilleri-says', 'Malta has a ‘strong case’ to continue to allow spring hunting, Clint Camilleri says', 'Gozo Minister Clint Camilleri firmly believes that Malta has a “strong case” to continue to allow spring hunting, despite the country facing infringement proceedings from the European Commission on the matter.In an interview with The Malta Independent, Camilleri said that Malta’s position on allowing spring hunting is backed by a court decision from the European Court of Justice.Malta has faced infringement proceedings from the European Commission on the spring hunting of turtle doves particularly, and these concerns were renewed when a moratorium on hunting the species in spring was lifted in 2022.European Commissioner for the Environment Virginius Sinkevicius told The Malta Independent on Sunday while in Malta on a visit that Malta must “cease the spring hunting of turtle doves.”“Malta is already subject to an infringement procedure for failure to enforce the protection of wild birds and the derogations allowing trapping and hunting and must ensure full compliance with EU law,” he had said while also pointing out that the Turtle Dove is a vulnerable species and that scientific data shows that it is in decline.Camilleri – who besides being responsible for Gozo, is also responsible for the hunting sector – was asked why the government continues to persist in allow spring hunting for this species when considering the infringement proceedings and Sinkevicius’ comments.Camilleri noted that maintaining the derogation was an electoral promise, and that the government will fulfil what it promised.He said that the European Commission must keep in mind the results of the 2015 referendum – where 50.44% voted for spring hunting to continue to be allowed, but also said that he understands that there is European legislation which must be followed.This being said, Camilleri noted that the European Court of Justice had ruled that hunting in autumn is not an alternative to hunting in spring – something which he said means that the ECJ agrees in principle that Malta may open a spring hunting season.Referring specifically to the Turtle Dove species, Camilleri noted that when applying a derogation for a hunting season, European legislation states that one needs to look at the ‘reference population’ – which is where the hunted species is coming from.He said that studies show that the reference population from where the species is coming to Malta is stable.  Asked whether these studies were conducted by hunting lobby FKNK, Camilleri said that they were not and were European studies.“We didn’t open the season just out of spite, but we opened it after a number of years of a moratorium and when we had the data to show that the population was stable, we opened a limited season… this isn’t a season of many months, it’s a season of 10 days where hunting is only allowed up until 12pm,” Camilleri said.He concluded that he feels that Malta has a strong case on the matter on the basis that it is backed up by a European court decision.Other parts of the interview with Clint Camilleri were publoished on Sunday and in The Malta Business Weekly', 'Gozo Minister Clint Camilleri firmly believes that Malta has a “strong case” to continue to allow spring hunting, despite the country facing infringement proceedings from the European Commission on the matter. In an interview with The Malta Independent , Camilleri said that Malta’s position on allowing spring hunting is backed by a court decision from the European Court of Justice. Malta has faced infringement proceedings from the European Commission on the spring hunting of turtle doves particularly, and these concerns were renewed when a moratorium on hunting the species in spring was lifted in 2022. European Commissioner for the Environment Virginius Sinkevicius told The Malta Independent on Sunday while in Malta on a visit that Malta must “cease the spring hunting of turtle doves.” “Malta is already subject to an infringement procedure for failure to enforce the protection of wild birds and the derogations allowing trapping and hunting and must ensure full compliance with EU law,” he had said while also pointing out that the Turtle Dove is a vulnerable species and that scientific data shows that it is in decline. Camilleri – who besides being responsible for Gozo, is also responsible for the hunting sector – was asked why the government continues to persist in allow spring hunting for this species when considering the infringement proceedings and Sinkevicius’ comments. Camilleri noted that maintaining the derogation was an electoral promise, and that the government will fulfil what it promised. He said that the European Commission must keep in mind the results of the 2015 referendum – where 50.44% voted for spring hunting to continue to be allowed, but also said that he understands that there is European legislation which must be followed. This being said, Camilleri noted that the European Court of Justice had ruled that hunting in autumn is not an alternative to hunting in spring – something which he said means that the ECJ agrees in principle that Malta may open a spring hunting season. Referring specifically to the Turtle Dove species, Camilleri noted that when applying a derogation for a hunting season, European legislation states that one needs to look at the ‘reference population’ – which is where the hunted species is coming from. He said that studies show that the reference population from where the species is coming to Malta is stable. Asked whether these studies were conducted by hunting lobby FKNK, Camilleri said that they were not and were European studies. “We didn’t open the season just out of spite, but we opened it after a number of years of a moratorium and when we had the data to show that the population was stable, we opened a limited season… this isn’t a season of many months, it’s a season of 10 days where hunting is only allowed up until 12pm,” Camilleri said. He concluded that he feels that Malta has a strong case on the matter on the basis that it is backed up by a European court decision.', 'https://www.independent.com.mt/file.aspx?f=233774', NULL, 'https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2023-07-10/local-news/Malta-has-a-strong-case-to-continue-to-allow-spring-hunting-Clint-Camilleri-says-6736253238', '2023-07-10 02:55:54', 'Malta', NULL, '2023-07-10 09:30:01', '2023-07-10 09:30:01', 2, NULL, '', 0),
(3345, 'MEA:-Eurobarometer-survey-highlights-the-pressing-need-to-separate-business-from-politics', 'MEA: Eurobarometer survey highlights the pressing need to separate business from politics', 'The Malta Employers’ Association stated Monday that the findings of the Eurobarometer on business and corruption are shocking, but not surprising. A survey published last week showed that nearly 90 per cent of those interviewed believe that corruption in Malta is rampant.For years, the association has been saying that the situation has been deteriorating, but there is an unwillingness to tackle the issues concretely, a statement said. We are now living in an environment where 87% of Maltese believe that corruption is part of the country’s business culture, and 79% see bribery and abuse of power as being rampant. It does not take Eurobarometer to conclude that many businesses believe that they can only succeed if they have the right political connections, with a majority stating that we have an issue with nepotism and patronage. The findings of the Eurobarometer reveal that there is no level playing field between businesses that is critical in ensuring a healthy competitive environment that generates investment and jobs. Rather, we are sliding a dangerous path that leads to equating entrepreneurship with opportunism, and that the concept of business success is more dependent on political contacts than it is on creative vision and risk taking. This does not bode well for both domestic and foreign direct investment, as more honest businesses will have to choose between either riding with the flow or to seek business opportunities elsewhere. Once again, MEA stresses the need to implement reforms that include: • A leaner parliament with full-time, better paid members. • Political parties will be exclusively state funded. All private donations and door to door collections will be illegal. • Full disclosure of contracts, remuneration, packages of persons of trust • Periodic independent audits of persons of trust to assess time spent, activities and results achieved • Number of persons on a position of trust will be capped • All contracts signed by government with third parties will be made public within 3 months from the date of signing • There will be no binding agreements with entities whose ultimate beneficiaries are unknown Parameters for public procurement through direct orders should be respected and enforced Although these proposals are fundamental, there is nothing controversial about them. They should appeal to anyone who believes that sustainable businesses and the well-being of society is dependent on a sound moral and ethical infrastructure to ensure that success and achievement are based on merit and hard work, rather than on political connections. The MEA said that although these issues have been raised at MCESD in the past, they need constant re-enforcement by the social partners to bring our politicians to their senses.', 'The Malta Employers’ Association stated Monday that the findings of the Eurobarometer on business and corruption are shocking, but not surprising. A survey published last week showed that nearly 90 per cent of those interviewed believe that corruption in Malta is rampant. For years, the association has been saying that the situation has been deteriorating, but there is an unwillingness to tackle the issues concretely, a statement said. We are now living in an environment where 87% of Maltese believe that corruption is part of the country’s business culture, and 79% see bribery and abuse of power as being rampant. It does not take Eurobarometer to conclude that many businesses believe that they can only succeed if they have the right political connections, with a majority stating that we have an issue with nepotism and patronage. The findings of the Eurobarometer reveal that there is no level playing field between businesses that is critical in ensuring a healthy competitive environment that generates investment and jobs. Rather, we are sliding a dangerous path that leads to equating entrepreneurship with opportunism, and that the concept of business success is more dependent on political contacts than it is on creative vision and risk taking. This does not bode well for both domestic and foreign direct investment, as more honest businesses will have to choose between either riding with the flow or to seek business opportunities elsewhere. Once again, MEA stresses the need to implement reforms that include: • A leaner parliament with full-time, better paid members. • Political parties will be exclusively state funded. All private donations and door to door collections will be illegal. • Full disclosure of contracts, remuneration, packages of persons of trust • Periodic independent audits of persons of trust to assess time spent, activities and results achieved • Number of persons on a position of trust will be capped • All contracts signed by government with third parties will be made public within 3 months from the date of signing • There will be no binding agreements with entities whose ultimate beneficiaries are unknown Parameters for public procurement through direct orders should be respected and enforced Although these proposals are fundamental, there is nothing controversial about them. They should appeal to anyone who believes that sustainable businesses and the well-being of society is dependent on a sound moral and ethical infrastructure to ensure that success and achievement are based on merit and hard work, rather than on political connections. The MEA said that although these issues have been raised at MCESD in the past, they need constant re-enforcement by the social partners to bring our politicians to their senses.', 'https://www.independent.com.mt/file.aspx?f=139334', NULL, 'https://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2023-07-10/local-news/MEA-Eurobarometer-survey-highlights-the-pressing-need-to-separate-business-from-politics-6736253237', '2023-07-10 02:55:54', 'Malta', NULL, '2023-07-10 09:30:01', '2023-07-10 09:30:01', 2, NULL, '', 0),
(3346, 'New-York-Torokorszag-luxus-oceanjaro-Megy-am-a-rongyrazas:-mutatjuk-hol-nyaralnak-iden-a-magyar-sztarok', 'New York, Törökország, luxus-óceánjáró ‒ Megy ám a rongyrázás: mutatjuk, hol nyaralnak idén a magyar sztárok', 'Élvezik a nyarat a magyar sztárok is! Érthető, hogy a tikkasztó hőségben elutaznak, és a legtöbben a vízparton élik túl a nagy meleget. Mutatjuk, hogy ki merre jár éppen!', 'Lékai-Kiss Ramóna Lékai-Kiss Ramóna és a férje, Lékai Máté New Yorkba látogattak el. A műsorvezető és a kézilabdázó több képet is posztoltak a nyaralásukról, sőt Kiss Ramóna már futott is egy nagyot a Central Parkban . Gelencsér Tímea Gelencsér Tímea nemrég Horvátorszból, Pag szigetről csekkolt be. A műsorvezető számára azonban nem csak strandolással telt a nyaralás, de egy jó nagyot buliztak is. Íme, a videó: Bombázó bikiniben Gelencsér Tímea ‒ fotó Tolvai Reni Tolvai Reni a magyar tengert választotta! Az énekesnő néhány nappal ezelőtt Siófokon napozott. Nádai Anikó Nádai Anikó a szomszédba, Szlovéniába látogatott el. A csinos műsorvezető a meseszép Bledi-tónál pózolt. Horváth Gréta A csinos influenszer Törökországban nyaral. A vakációról több fotót is megosztott. Gáspárék Gáspár Beáéknak szintén Törökország az idei úti céljuk. Hódi Pamela Hódi Pamela a férjével és a két kislányával Horvátországban nyaral. Az influenszer félt, hogy milyen lesz a hosszú út a kisebbik gyermekével, de szerencsére minden a legnagyobb rendben ment. A teljes posztot ide kattintva tekintheti meg. Jákob Zoltán Jákob Zoltán mindig nyaral, de ezúttal egy luxus-óceánjárót választott, ahová a gyerekeit is magával vitte. A Nagy Ő a két lakosztály egyikét vette ki a lányainak és a saját magának. Pintér Adrienn Ada is a Balatonról csekkolt be.', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.blikk.hu/sztarvilag/hazai-sztarok/magyar-sztarok-nyaralas-gelencser-timea-tolvai-reni-kiss-ramona/6j3y44z', '2023-07-10 02:51:59', 'hungary', NULL, '2023-07-10 09:30:01', '2023-07-10 09:30:01', 2, 'Sztárvilág', '', 0),
(3347, 'Perez-\"not-too-concerned\"-by-challenge-of-reversing-five-race-qualifying-slump-or-2023-British-Grand-Prix', 'Perez “not too concerned” by challenge of reversing five-race qualifying slump | 2023 British Grand Prix', 'Sergio Perez is confident he will be able to reverse his recent poor run of results in qualifying, which he will work on in the Red Bull simulator this week.', 'Sergio Perez is confident he will be able to reverse his recent poor run of results in qualifying, which continued last weekend. Advert | Become a Supporter & go ad-free Perez will work on the difficulties he’s had in a session on the Red Bull simulator today. “I think it’s just the amount of details,” he explained. “I have become a little bit more sensitive to the car in the last few races, especially on Saturday when on low fuel. It’s something that I’m going to be working on already from tomorrow [Monday] in the simulator with the team. “We have some ideas [about] how we operate in such a small window of detail. It’s just that we need a strong Saturday and the positive thing is that the pace is there on Sundays where at the end of the day the points are given. But we just have to sort it out and have a clean weekend because the pace is there.” Rain has affected several of the last five qualifying sessions, which Perez said has contributed to his difficulties in the car. “I think it’s with my driving, how I am approaching the Saturdays, how we are doing it as a team. We just have to figure it out, the amount of detail. For example, the last qualifying [sessions] that I’ve had they’ve been in changeable conditions and it’s where a lot of detail comes in play.” Advert | Become a RaceFans supporter and go ad-free “So I’m not too concerned, I think we had a great Friday in terms of pace, we just have to sort out the qualifying and we’ll be fine.” Perez finished yesterday’s race sixth after lining up 15th on the grid. “Nothing worked today,” he said afterwards. “I had a great launch, but then I was pushed off by Ocon on lap one. I lost positions instead of gaining, so it just made it harder, the recovery.” He collided with Nico Hulkenberg at one stage as he tried to make up ground. “We clipped, I think I was lucky to not get a puncture,” Perez said, calling it “a little race incident.” He lost further ground when he pitted shortly before the Safety Car was deployed. “I used too much my tyres on the first stint, and then we boxed I think three laps before the Safety Car. So it wasn’t meant to be, but in the end we we gave it all and we did what we possibly could.” Despite having fallen 99 points behind Verstappen in the championship, Perez remained upbeat about his chances over the remainder of the season. “We’re making a lot of progress because the pace is there on Sundays,” he said. “But it’s just the whole weekend overall. We’ve had a few bad weekends but at the end of the day it only matters where we finish in Abu Dhabi. “So it’s a long season still, and I fully believe that I can get my season back on-track.” RaceFans strives to bring its readers news directly from the key players in Formula 1. We are able to do this thanks in part to the generous backing of our RaceFans Supporters. By contributing £1 per month or £12 per year (or the equivalent in other currencies) you can help cover the costs involved in producing original journalism: Travelling, writing, creating, hosting, contacting and developing. We have been proudly supported by our readers for over 10 years. If you enjoy our independent coverage, please consider becoming a RaceFans Supporter today. As a bonus, all our Supporters can also browse the site ad-free. Sign up or find out more via the links below: Advert | Become a RaceFans supporter and go ad-free', NULL, NULL, 'https://www.racefans.net/2023/07/10/perez-not-too-concerned-by-challenge-of-reversing-five-race-qualifying-slump/', '2023-07-10 02:50:47', 'united kingdom', NULL, '2023-07-10 09:30:01', '2023-07-10 09:30:01', 7, '2023 British Grand Prix articles;2023 F1 season articles;F1 news;Formula 1;2023 British Grand Prix;British Grand Prix;F1;F1 Great Britain;F1 Great Britain 2023;f1 silverstone;formula 1;Grand Prix of Great Britain;perez;Red Bull;red bull f1 team;red bull r', '', 0);
